E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETech%20billionaires%2C%20like%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20are%20embracing%20fashion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20fashion%20expert%20said%20it's%20because%20they're%20seeking%20cultural%20relevance%20and%20legacy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStill%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20one-sided%20relationship%3A%20Fashion%20is%20courting%20tech%2C%20too.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20of%20fashion%20has%20witnessed%20a%20consistent%20pattern%20for%20some%20time%20now%3A%20Big%20Tech%20billionaires%20gradually%20entering%20its%20orbit%20from%20the%20edges%20until%20they've%20found%20themselves%20at%20its%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20last%20month%2C%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Priscilla%20Chan's%20presence%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-and-priscilla-chan-wear-matching-prada-loafers-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efront%20row%20at%20the%20Prada%20Fall%2FWinter%202026%20collection%3C%2Fa%3E%20stirred%20the%20fashion%20world%2C%20amid%20Meta's%20ambition%20to%20up%20the%20luxury%20factor%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-ai-meta-glasses-ray-ban-orion-2025-earnings-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20glasses.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20glances%20over%20prove%20that%20this%20was%20not%20an%20isolated%20case.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAmazon%20magnate%20Jeff%20Bezos%20and%20Laura%20S%C3%A1nchez-Bezos%20have%20long%20been%20fashion%20enthusiasts%2C%20with%20the%20fashion%20world%20courting%20them%20and%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flauren-sanchez-jeff-bezos-love-makes-them-relateable-vogue-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVogue%20cover%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20roles%20as%20lead%20donors%20to%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmet-gala-theme-dress-code-cochairs-event-details-2026%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%202026%20Met%20Gala%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decision%20Anna%20Wintour%20defended%20amid%20backlash.%20Persistent%2C%20if%20unfounded%2C%20rumors%20that%20Bezos%20could%20acquire%20Cond%C3%A9%20Nast.%20Add%20strategic%20appearances%20with%20Wintour%2C%20front-row%20seats%20at%20Schiaparelli%20and%20Dior%20couture%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-roach-celebrity-stylist-interview-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELaw%20Roach%3C%2Fa%3E-styled%20vintage%20Versace%20moments%2C%20and%20the%20idea%20becomes%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20tech%20billionaires%20attending%20the%20right%20places%20and%20hanging%20with%20the%20right%20people%2C%20their%20place%20in%20fashion%20feels%20less%20like%20a%20cameo%20and%20more%20set%20in%20stone.%20It's%20no%20longer%20up%20for%20debate.%20What%20is%2C%20though%2C%20is%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Why%20%3Cem%3Efashion%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%20One%20expert%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it's%20about%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22367bfc38-b2d1-43e4-a026-d659e48b2721%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20indifference%20to%20front%20row%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20early%20days%2C%20fashion%20has%20gone%20hand%20in%20hand%20with%20the%20elite%20class.%20It's%20what%20they%20consumed%2C%20financed%2C%20and%20promoted.%20The%20situation%20hasn't%20changed%20much.%20Look%20around%2C%20and%20conglomerates%20like%20LVMH%20and%20Kering%2C%20as%20well%20as%20celebrities%2C%20still%20largely%20influence%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20evolved%2C%20however%2C%20is%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Priscilla%20Chan%20and%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20at%20a%202026%20Prada%20runway%20show%20in%20Milan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a072171fb3fcb426488044%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPriscilla%20Chan%20and%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20at%20a%202026%20Prada%20runway%20show%20in%20Milan.%3Cp%3EAlessandro%20Garofalo%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSocial%20media%20has%20changed%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20fashion%20journalist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Flouispisano%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELouis%20Pisano%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20become%20really%20image-conscious%20in%20a%20way%20that%20we%20previously%20only%20saw%20in%20celebrities.%20Now%2C%20everyone%20needs%20to%20brand%20themselves%20because%20everyone%20knows%20that%20every%20moment%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20make%20an%20impression.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20before%2C%20tech%20bros%20were%20famously%20indifferent%20toward%20fashion%20%E2%80%94%20think%20of%20Steve%20Jobs%2C%20who%20proudly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs-turtleneck-2011-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewore%20a%20black%20turtleneck%20and%20jeans%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20today%2C%20even%20they%20seem%20susceptible%20to%20the%20constant%20presence%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPisano%20points%20to%20an%20Instagram%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fpriscillachan%2Freel%2FDVOqO4AgBmv%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereel%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20by%20Chan%20that%20felt%20distinctly%20TikToky%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20if%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20were%20lifestyle%20influencers%20casually%20strolling%20through%20Milan%20and%20Prada.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBeing%20mindful%20about%20social%20media%20is%20one%20thing.%20Venturing%20into%20fashion's%20gatekept%20inner%20circle%20is%20another.%20In%20an%20appearance-driven%20culture%2C%20coolness%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20validation%20that%20comes%20with%20it%20%E2%80%94%20still%20matters%20above%20all%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20be%20a%20tech%20bro%2C%20and%20if%20you're%20badly%20dressed%2C%20everybody's%20still%20gonna%20be%20like%2C%20'You%20look%20like%20shit%2C'%26quot%3B%20Pisano%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20all%20of%20this%20money%2C%20so%20why%20not%20look%20great%20as%20well%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20looking%20great%20here%20isn't%20about%20self-expression.%20It's%20about%20access%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20cultural%20legitimacy%20money%20alone%20can't%20automatically%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lauren%20S%C3%A1nchez%20and%20Jeff%20Bezos%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b57643a96e437d6eb853de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226685%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELauren%20S%C3%A1nchez%20and%20Jeff%20Bezos%20attend%20the%20Christian%20Dior%20Haute%20Couture%20Week%20Spring%2FSummer%202026%20show%20as%20part%20of%20Paris%20Fashion%20Week%20on%20January%2026%2C%202026%20in%20Paris%2C%20France.%3Cp%3EAnthony%20Ghnassia%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Christian%20Dior%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJoshua%20Graham%2C%20fashion%20editor%20at%20Rolling%20Stone%20UK%2C%20compared%20the%20entrance%20of%20tech%20bros%20into%20the%20high%20fashion%20world%20with%20Mark%20Mylod's%20film%20%26quot%3BThe%20Menu%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20a%20group%20of%20rich%20people%20go%20to%20an%20exclusive%20restaurant%20but%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20really%20care%20about%20the%20food%2C%20just%20that%20they're%20able%20to%20be%20seen%20within%20the%20context%20of%20what%20the%20best%20looks%20like.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPisano%20voiced%20a%20similar%20point%3A%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20fashion%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20easiest%20pathways%20to%20cultural%20relevance%20simply%20because%20it's%20an%20exclusive%20framework.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20let%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%2C%20after%20all%2C%20a%20business%20where%20brands%20and%20money%20tend%20to%20speak%20louder%20than%20individual%20style%2C%20and%20wearing%20the%20right%20label%20and%20knowing%20the%20right%20names%20becomes%20fashion%20shorthand%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20entry%20pass%20to%20culture's%20apex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222204db19-3912-48ae-a8ec-37ad8dd8c691%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBillionaires%20want%20staying%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20billionaires%20used%20to%20building%20platforms%2C%20cultural%20legacy%20is%20the%20next%20frontier.%20%26quot%3BWearing%20an%20independent%20label%20isn't%20going%20to%20bring%20you%20as%20much%20cultural%20cachet%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprada-miu-miu-stock-beating-luxury-slump-lvmh-kering-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewearing%20Prada%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20custom%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flouis-vuitton-beauty-lipstick-consumer-sentiment-luxury-slowdown-splurge-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELouis%20Vuitton%3C%2Fa%3E%20piece%2C%26quot%3B%20Pisano%20noted.%20Indeed%2C%20symbolic%20power%20is%20still%20the%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E''It'll%20immortalize%20them%2C''%20Pisano%20said%20of%20tech%20billionaires'%20aligning%20with%20luxury%20houses.%20Prada%20has%20been%20around%20since%201913.%20Schiaparelli%20since%201927.%20Dior%20since%201946.%20You%20get%20the%20picture.%20''They%20want%20to%20attach%20themselves%20onto%20something%20that%20they're%20betting%20is%20going%20to%20live%20forever%20because%20social%20media%20platforms%20die%20out.%20New%20ones%20will%20come%2C%20but%20you're%20always%20going%20to%20need%20clothes%20to%20wear.''%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20moguls%20have%20already%20had%20a%20hand%20in%20shaping%20society's%20tastes%20and%20lifestyles%20thanks%20to%20the%20technology%20they've%20created.%20%26quot%3BThey%20control%20the%20algorithms%20and%20build%20the%20infrastructure%2C%26quot%3B%20Pisano%20continued.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20he%20makes%20the%20point%20that%20it's%20not%20a%20one-sided%20relationship.%20Perhaps%2C%20billionaires%20are%20already%20fashion%20people%20after%20all.%20%26quot%3BDesigners%20need%20these%20people%20in%20order%20to%20push%20their%20content%20out%20to%20shopping%20recommendations%2C%26quot%3B%20Pisano%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraham%20echoes%20this%20view%2C%20adding%20that%20fashion%20houses%20need%20to%20court%20relationships%20with%20tech%20titans%20because%2C%20ultimately%2C%20labels%20are%20always%20seeking%20exponential%20growth.%20''I%20understand%20why%20anyone%20would%20want%20to%20work%20with%20Zuckerberg%2C''%20the%20editor%20said.%20''The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-oil-price-shock-us-iran-war-economic-impact-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeconomy%20everywhere%20is%20in%20the%20toilet%3C%2Fa%3E.''%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226744%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Priscilla%20Chan%20and%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a085e3e8408f66718052af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224546%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPriscilla%20Chan%20and%20Mark%20Zuckerberg.%3Cp%3EANGELA%20WEISS%20%2F%20AFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20many%20were%20scrunching%20their%20faces%2C%20wondering%20why%20Zuckerberg%20was%20pushing%20himself%20to%20the%20front%20row%20at%20Prada%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20the%20relationship%20between%20tech%20and%20fashion%20is%20more%20symbiotic.%20Brands%20are%20increasingly%20turning%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-giants-build-ai-future-creators-less-power-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20instead%20of%20creatives%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20danger%2C%20Graham%20warned%2C%20is%20that%20when%20billionaires%20invest%20in%20fashion%2C%20they%20should%20at%20least%20pay%20attention%20to%20emerging%20designers%20who%20do%20it%20for%20the%20love%20of%20the%20art%20form.%20He%20added%20that%20so%20many%20creatives%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falexander-mcqueen-legendary-fashion-designer-life-career%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20late%20Lee%20Alexander%20McQueen%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20not%20enter%20the%20fashion%20world%20to%20''make%20a%20quick%20buck%2C''%20but%20because%20it%20was%20their%20passion.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E''I%20don't%20know%20if%20it%20would%20be%20smarter%20for%20billionaires%20to%20go%20to%20a%20Central%20Saint%20Martin%20show%20and%20pick%20out%20a%20few%20students%20that%20they%20loved%2C''%20Graham%20argued%2C%20referencing%20the%20graduate%20show%20held%20by%20the%20prestigious%20London%20art%20and%20design%20school.%20''But%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20way%20for%20us%20to%20find%20ourselves%20back%20in%20a%20place%20where%20the%20patronage%20of%20fashion%20isn't%20so%20commercial.''%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraham%2C%20like%20many%20who%20questioned%20why%20Zuckerberg%20was%20sitting%20front%20row%2C%20said%20he%20can%20understand%20the%20critique.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20very%20hypercritical%20of%20something%20like%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it's%20because%20they%20care%20%26quot%3Babout%20what%20a%20designer%2C%20a%20garment%2C%20a%20shoe%20says%20about%20you%20as%20a%20person%20and%20then%20says%20about%20society%20as%20a%20whole.''%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20though%2C%20the%20relationship%20between%20tech%20and%20fashion%20will%20continue%20to%20evolve.%20Tech%20may%20control%20the%20feed%2C%20but%20fashion%20still%20controls%20the%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-tech-billionaires-zuckerberg-bezos-high-fashion-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773500205000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b0236582b35e2c04dd69f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-tech-billionaires-zuckerberg-bezos-high-fashion-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tech%20bros%20were%20famously%20indifferent%20toward%20fashion%2C%20but%20now%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20and%20other%20tech%20billionaires%20are%20embracing%20it.%20Here's%20why.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Beatriz%20Reitz%20Gameiro)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-tech-billionaires-zuckerberg-bezos-high-fashion-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Marines%20are%20on%20the%20hunt%20for%20a%20cloak%20they%20can%20wear%20to%20hide%20themselves%20from%20thermal-imaging%20sensors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224473%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marines%20evacuate%20simulated%20casualties%20during%20an%20exercise%20at%20Marine%20Corps%20Base%20Hawaii%2C%20Nov.%205%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b36961a7a4f9df67ba4651%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222982%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarines%20evacuate%20simulated%20casualties%20during%20an%20exercise%20at%20Marine%20Corps%20Base%20Hawaii%2C%20Nov.%205%2C%202025.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Marine%20Corps%20photo%20by%20Lance%20Cpl.%20Tania%20Guerrero%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Marine%20Corps%20is%20seeking%20a%20company%20to%20develop%20a%20new%20outer%20garment%20for%20protection.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20cloak%20would%20shield%20Marines%20from%20enemy%20thermal-imaging%20sensors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThermal-imaging%20sensors%20are%20prolific%20in%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20often%20used%20on%20drones.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Marine%20Corps%20is%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20outer%20garment%20to%20protect%20its%20troops%20from%20battlefield%20threats%20that%20can%20see%20through%20traditional%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-armys-new-camouflage-will-allow-soldiers-to-hide-in-plain-sight-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecamouflage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20concealment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20modern%20battlefield%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farmy-leaders-warn-modern-warfare-is-overwhelming-commanders-with-data-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaturated%20with%20sensors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20thermal-imaging%20technology%20that%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-arctic-artillery-forces-learn-dig-hide-move-dodge-drones-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetect%20human%20and%20vehicle%20heat%20signatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20infrared%20range%20of%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum.%20Many%20of%20the%20drones%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20are%20equipped%20with%20thermal-imaging%20cameras%20that%20have%20been%20used%20to%20deadly%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20troops%20have%20sought%20solutions%2C%20and%20now%2C%20so%20are%20US%20Marines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Marines%20published%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bsources%20sought%26quot%3B%20notification%20on%20Wednesday%20announcing%20the%20service's%20search%20for%20vendors%20who%20could%20create%20a%20camouflage%20to%20reduce%20the%20chance%20of%20infrared%20detection%2C%20calling%20the%20desired%20garment%20a%20%26quot%3BMultispectral%20Camouflage%20Overgarment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20said%20it%20will%20deliver%20%26quot%3Bindividual%20signature%20management%26quot%3B%20by%20%26quot%3Bmitigating%20detection%20across%20the%20visual%2C%20near%20infrared%2C%20and%20short-wave%20infrared%20spectrums%20as%20well%20as%20suppress%20thermal%20signatures%20in%20the%20mid-wave%20infrared%20and%20long%20wave%20infrared%20to%20reduce%20the%20likelihood%20of%20detection%20by%20thermal%20sensors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20garment%20is%20intended%20to%20mask%20how%20a%20Marine%20appears%20not%20only%20to%20the%20naked%20eye%20and%20night%20vision%20devices%2C%20but%20also%20to%20advanced%20infrared%20and%20thermal%20sensors%20used%20by%20drones%20and%20surveillance%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20accomplish%20that%20aim%2C%20the%20Corps%20is%20seeking%20%26quot%3Ba%20single-piece%2C%20generously-sized%20draped%20design%20constructed%20to%20provide%20full-body%20coverage%2C%20including%20individual%20gear%20and%20equipment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20said.%20It%20must%20be%20capable%20of%20being%20donned%20within%2015%20seconds%2C%20over%20a%20Marine's%20uniform%20and%20equipment%2C%20whether%20deployed%20or%20during%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cloak%20could%20significantly%20reduce%20the%20distance%20from%20which%20Marines%20are%20detected%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20adversaries%20to%20spot%20them%20using%20both%20ground-based%20and%20aerial%20sensors.%20It%20must%20also%20function%20in%20extreme%20temperatures%20and%20varied%20environmental%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20service%20says%20it%20intends%20to%20have%20more%20than%2061%2C000%20of%20the%20cloaks%20available%20to%20troops%20by%20fiscal%20year%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20has%20long%20recognized%20the%20need%20for%20such%20a%20capability%2C%20but%20the%20extreme%20proliferation%20of%20sensors%20aboard%20cheap%20drones%20in%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20heightened%20the%20urgency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20adversary%20%5Btarget%5D%20acquisition%20systems%20are%20very%2C%20very%20capable%20in%20that%2C%20if%20you%20can%20see%20a%20target%2C%20with%20precision%20munitions%20...%20you%20can%20hit%20a%20target%2C%26quot%3B%20Gen.%20Mark%20Milley%2C%20then%20the%20Army's%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20told%20lawmakers%20in%202019.%20%26quot%3BSo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexperts-push-the-limits-to-defeat-this-threat-to-concealed-soldiers-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecamouflage%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20break%20up%20electronic%20signatures%20and%20break%20up%20heat%20signatures%20are%20critical.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Secretary%20of%20the%20Army%20Dan%20Driscoll%20spoke%20bluntly%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farmy-secretary-says-tanks-must-avoid-cheap-drone-attacks-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emodern%20battlefield%20in%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20War%20on%20the%20Rocks%20podcast%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Byou%20cannot%20move%20without%20being%20seen.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20would%20require%20changes%20in%20how%20ground%20forces%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%2056th%20Separate%20Motorized%20Infantry%20Mariupol%20Brigade%20shared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fwatch%2F%3Fv%3D4253070268166031%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideo%20footage%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20March%20of%20its%20efforts%20to%20combat%20thermal%20imaging%2C%20presenting%20what%20it%20described%20as%20anti-thermal%20suits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20fantasy.%20It%20is%20the%20reality%20of%20modern%20warfare%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2056th%20said%20in%20a%20caption%20posted%20alongside%20the%20video%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThermal%20imaging%20suits%20are%20changing%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20battlefield%2C%20making%20soldiers%20invisible%20to%20enemy%20thermal-imaging%20cameras%20and%20drones.%20Such%20technologies%20are%20critical%20for%20assault%20teams%2C%20reconnaissance%2C%20snipers%2C%20and%20even%20evacuation%20missions.%20And%20this%20is%20just%20the%20beginning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarines-looking-for-a-cloak-to-hide-from-thermal-imaging-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773500161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b36978a96e437d6eb84022%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarines-looking-for-a-cl